   GLEASON CORP. (Rochester, N.Y.) -- James S. Gleason,
chairman and president of this maker of gear production
equipment, was also named president of the Gleason Works
Division. He succeeds Richard J. Bonnie, who resigned. Also,
William J. Flaherty, president of the company's Component's
Group, was named vice president, operations, of the division.
Gleason is selling its Components Group. Gleason said the
moves, including moving the corporate headquarters to the
Gleason Works in Rochester, are aimed at refocusing on its
core business.
